content:
How can I calculate the average time it takes for a company to fill a job position, from the initial posting to the hiring decision? For example, if a job was posted on January 1st and the position was filled on February 15th, what is the average time it takes for the company to fill a position? 
Here is the HTML code that displays the calculated result:
<p>The job was posted on January 1st and was filled on February 15th.</p>
<p>The average time to fill a position is:</p>
<script>
var startDate = new Date("January 1, 2021");
var endDate = new Date("February 15, 2021");
var timeDiff = Math.abs(endDate.getTime() - startDate.getTime());
var avgTime = Math.ceil(timeDiff / (1000 * 3600 * 24));
document.write(avgTime + " days");
</script>
